decks.notes: This Boros Aggro deck focuses on quick and aggressive creature plays, supported by burn spells and disruptive elements like Ranger-Captain of Eos and Static Prison. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a combination of efficient creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Seasoned Pyromancer, while also utilizing versatile spells like Galvanic Discharge and Thraben Charm for removal and disruption. With a mix of direct damage, creature synergy, and disruptive elements, this deck aims to apply pressure early and maintain board control to secure a victory.

The deck focuses on utilizing aggressive creatures like Phlage, Ragavan, and Phelia to quickly apply pressure on the opponent while controlling the board with cards like Solitude and Consign to Memory. Teferi, Time Raveler helps to protect the board and disrupt the opponent's strategies. Quantum Riddler and Fable of the Mirror-Breaker provide card advantage and tempo advantage. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a combination of aggressive creatures and disruptive spells, creating a challenging board state for the opponent to deal with.

The deck focuses on a mix of aggressive creatures and disruptive spells to control the game and pressure the opponent. By utilizing cards like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phage, Titan of Fire's Fury, the deck aims to deal damage quickly while using cards like Teferi, Time Raveler and Prismatic Ending to disrupt the opponent's strategy. The inclusion of cards like Solitude and Consign to Memory provide additional removal options, allowing the deck to maintain control of the battlefield. This deck operates on a proactive aggro strategy with elements of disruption to keep the opponent off balance.

The main concept of this Modern 1 vs 1 Aggro - Affinity deck is to quickly flood the battlefield with artifact creatures and use powerful artifacts to disrupt the opponent's strategy. The deck utilizes cards like Memnite, Pinnacle Emissary, and Kappa Cannoneer to put pressure on the opponent while utilizing cards like Metallic Rebuke and Engineered Explosives to control the board. The deck also includes powerful artifacts like Mox Opal and Mishra's Bauble to generate mana and draw cards, further pushing its aggressive game plan. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent quickly before they can establish their own game plan.

This deck utilizes a toolbox of creatures to create combos and generate value by sacrificing, tutoring, and recurring creatures. Utilizing cards like Chord of Calling, Grist, the Hunger Tide, and Yawgmoth, Thran Physician, the deck aims to establish a board presence while disrupting the opponent's game plan. The inclusion of cards like Carrion Feeder, Cauldron Familiar, and Viscera Seer allows for efficient sacrifice outlets to trigger various abilities and combos. The deck thrives on synergy between its creatures and spells to create a powerful and resilient board state.

This deck aims to disrupt opponents' game plans with a combination of targeted removal, hand disruption, and flicker effects. By utilizing creatures like Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd and Witch Enchanter to generate value, as well as powerful spells like Fatal Push and Thoughtseize, this deck aims to control the board while applying pressure with creatures like Overlord of the Balemurk. The inclusion of Teferi, Time Raveler and Ephemerate provides additional versatility and disruption, making it difficult for opponents to establish a strong board presence. The deck's mana base is designed to support its aggressive game plan while also providing access to powerful multicolored spells.

The main concept of this deck is to generate a large amount of mana quickly through rituals and medallions, while using Ral, Monsoon Mage to copy spells and deal damage. The deck also utilizes card draw, impulse spells, and recursion with Past in Flames to keep the combo going. The goal is to assemble the necessary pieces to cast a large Grapeshot to finish off the opponent in one explosive turn. Overall, the deck focuses on fast mana generation, spell copying, and explosive finishes.

The main concept of this deck is to utilize the combination of Simic cards with the Birthing Ritual card to generate mana quickly and efficiently, allowing for a fast-paced aggressive strategy. The deck focuses on deploying creatures like Abhorrent Oculus and Shardless Agent early on, while also having access to control elements like Flare of Denial and Sink into Stupor to disrupt the opponent's game plan. The inclusion of cards like Endurance and Subtlety provide additional versatility to handle various threats. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a combination of speed and disruption.

This deck aims to quickly flood the board with cheap artifact creatures and utilize cards like Mox Opal and Springleaf Drum to accelerate its mana production. The deck also utilizes Urza's Saga and Emry, Lurker of the Loch to generate value from the graveyard and create additional threats. It includes disruptive elements like Tormod's Crypt and Pithing Needle to disrupt the opponent's game plan while maintaining a fast and aggressive pace with cards like Galvanic Blast and Pinnacle Emissary. The overall strategy is to overwhelm the opponent with a combination of speed and disruption.

The deck focuses on utilizing instant reanimation spells like Goryo's Vengeance to bring back powerful creatures such as Griselbrand and Atraxa, Grand Unifier from the graveyard for explosive plays. It also includes disruptive spells like Thoughtseize and Force of Negation to control the opponent's game plan. Ephemerate is used to generate additional value by blinking key creatures like Psychic Frog or Solitude. The deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces while disrupting the opponent's strategy, ultimately aiming to win through powerful creature attacks or overwhelming the opponent with card advantage.

This deck focuses on aggressive gameplay while also utilizing disruptive elements to slow down the opponent. It aims to control the board and disrupt the opponent's strategy while quickly building a strong board presence. The deck includes powerful creatures like Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury, along with control cards like Teferi, Time Raveler and Wrath of the Skies. The deck also includes ways to protect its creatures and generate card advantage, creating a versatile and effective strategy that can quickly overwhelm opponents.

The key concept of this deck is to utilize aggressive creatures like Monastery Swiftspear and Slickshot Show-Off, along with efficient burn spells like Lightning Bolt and Lava Dart, to quickly reduce the opponent's life total. The deck aims to apply early pressure and maintain tempo advantage by drawing cards with cards like Mishra's Bauble and Preordain. Additionally, the deck includes pump spells like Mutagenic Growth and Violent Urge to enhance the aggressiveness of the creatures. The mana base allows for consistent casting of spells and utilizing fetch lands to thin the deck and trigger abilities.

This deck focuses on assembling a variety of creatures to create a powerful and synergistic toolbox of abilities. By using cards like Chord of Calling and Birthing Ritual, the deck can quickly search for and play key creatures like Cauldron Familiar, Skyclave Apparition, and Yawgmoth, Thran Physician. The deck also includes sacrifice outlets like Carrion Feeder and Viscera Seer to take advantage of creatures entering the battlefield and trigger abilities. With a mix of utility creatures and ways to tutor for them, the deck aims to create a versatile and adaptable strategy to outmaneuver opponents.

The main concept of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creature spells and burn spells. The deck focuses on quick creature plays like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury, while also utilizing burn spells like Galvanic Discharge and Goblin Bombardment to clear the way for attacks. The inclusion of cards like Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Ranger-Captain of Eos provide additional utility and options for different situations. The mana base is built around fetch lands and dual lands to ensure consistent color access for the deck's spells.

The key strategy of this UW Control deck is to maintain control of the game by utilizing a mix of counterspells, removal, and card advantage. The deck focuses on controlling the board through cards like Wrath of the Skies and Supreme Verdict, while also disrupting the opponent's game plan with cards like Spell Snare and Force of Negation. The inclusion of powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Hero of Dominaria and Narset, Parter of Veils provides additional card advantage and control options. The deck aims to outvalue the opponent and control the game until it can secure a win condition.

The deck focuses on quickly ramping up mana with cards like Birthing Ritual and Shardless Agent to efficiently cast powerful creatures and spells. It utilizes a variety of disruptive abilities such as Force of Negation and Sink into Stupor to control the board and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck also includes a mix of card advantage engines like Coiling Oracle and Ice-Fang Coatl to keep the resources flowing. Overall, the strategy revolves around aggressive plays and tempo advantage to overwhelm the opponent and secure a quick victory.
